        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 4:28PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 427 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Pageland, or 15 miles south of Monroe, moving
east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph with a brief tornado possible.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Cheraw, Pageland, Chesterfield, Cheraw State Park, Northeastern
Technical College, Cheraw Municipal Airport, Ruby, Mount Croghan,
McFarlan, Chesterfield Ruby Middle School, High Point Fire Station,
Cheraw Fish Hatchery, Tradesville, Chesterfield Detention Center, and
Central High School.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central South Carolina.</instruction>
